cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper is about object detection using a new approach that simplifies the task as a center and scale prediction task through convolutions. This approach is applied to pedestrian and face detection, which are both subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of modern deep models, which suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of convolution, which is a common technique in neural networks and signal processing, indicating a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
